        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I think it makes sense to have default metadata for {{Zend_Cloud_StorageService_Adapter_S3}} which is then used in the {{storeItem()}} call, if no metadata is passed to {{storeItem()}} explicitly.\r\n\r\nThat way, the {{storeItem()}} call can remain storage service adapter agnostic.\r\n\r\n\r\n-Looking at http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.cloud.storageservice.html#zend.cloud.storageservice.adapters.options it seems that the 'metadata' option, when passed as part of the options in the constructor, is supposed to affect storeItem(). At the moment this is ignored, however. So setting metadata needs to be done on the storeItem() call explicitly, which breaks the abstraction that Zend_Cloud otherwise provides.-"
        },
